   <abstract displayLabel="Description">P.D. Montgomery discusses his opinion of southerners and his religious beliefs.</abstract>
   <note type="biographical/historical" displayLabel="Biographical Note">Captain Peter D. Montgomery served in Company H, 6th Michigan Infantry (later reorganized as the 1st Regiment Michigan Heavy Artillery) during the Civil War. He was stationed first at Ft. McKim in Baltimore. In Louisiana, he was at Camp Parapet in Carollton, Baton Rouge, Port Hudson, Camp Dudley in New Orleans, and Camp Mors. He was wounded at Port Hudson and resigned his commission in August 1864 as a result of his wounds.</note>
